SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 687
By Yager
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize WIN Learning on the
occasion of its thirtieth anniversary.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause in their
deliberations to pay tribute to those exemplary Tennessee companies that, through their
unwavering commitment to education and workforce development, significantly enhance the
lives of citizens across the State and beyond; and
WHEREAS, WIN Learning, founded in 1996 and headquartered in Kingston, stands as a
beacon of innovation in career readiness, having provided integrated e-learning solutions—
including academic and employability skills courseware, assessments, and credentials—to
empower individuals for success in college, trade school, the military, or the workplace; and
WHEREAS, over the past three decades, WIN Learning has equipped more than ten
million learners worldwide with the essential tools, confidence, and skills necessary to excel in
their careers and lives, with its impactful programs extending throughout the United States
through partnerships with school districts, community colleges, workforce development
agencies, and statewide initiatives in multiple states; and
WHEREAS, the mission of WIN Learning is to ensure that all learners and job seekers
have a positive future and a clear pathway to success by preparing them to be both career-
ready and life-ready, aligning with the values of education, opportunity, and community that
define the Volunteer State; and
WHEREAS, as WIN Learning celebrates its thirtieth anniversary in 2026, it continues to
lead in delivering research-based solutions that bridge the gap between education and
employment, fostering economic growth and personal achievement for countless individuals
across the nation; and
SJR0687
012555
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the success of this State, the strength of our communities, and the vitality of
our workforce depend, in great measure, upon the dedication of organizations like WIN
Learning, which use their expertise and resources to build brighter futures for all; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and congratulate WIN
Learning upon reaching the milestone of its thirtieth anniversary, recognizing its invaluable
contributions to career readiness and workforce development across this State and throughout
the country and extending our best wishes for continued success in the years to come.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
